Provenance
----------
The RRT exercise is derived from soamsy/Syllogimous-v3
(https://github.com/soamsy/Syllogimous-v3), itself descended from
Syllogimous by 4skinSkywalker and Syllogimous-v3 by ikokusovereignty,
all under CC BY-NC 3.0 — this license therefore applies to Cerevana as
a whole.

The N-Back exercise is an original JavaScript reimplementation of the
dual n-back protocol popularized by Brain Workshop (Paul Hoskinson and
Jonathan Toomim, GPL-2.0). It shares no code with Brain Workshop, which
is credited as inspiration.

The Quad Box exercise is built on the game engine of soamsy/quad-box
(https://github.com/soamsy/quad-box), MIT-licensed; the engine code in
js/quadbox/engine/ is near-verbatim upstream code (per-file attribution
headers), its license is kept at js/quadbox/LICENSE, and the full
derivation is documented in js/quadbox/PROVENANCE.md. The MIT-licensed
Quad Box code is not subject to this repository's CC BY-NC terms.

Bundled third-party assets carry their own licenses: Space Grotesk and
Zen Dots typefaces (SIL OFL 1.1, see fonts/), menu background photo by
Simon Berger (Pexels License), Chart.js (MIT, vendored in js/lib/).
